messages.message:
Patch Set 1:

If anyone wants to test this, I used a kind cluster and the nginx controller as documented at https://kind.sigs.k8s.io/docs/user/ingress/. The ingress service for voltha i defined is

apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  annotations:
    kubernetes.io/ingress.class: "nginx"
    nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/ssl-redirect: "true"
    nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/backend-protocol: "GRPC"
    nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/grpc-backend: "true"
  name: voltha-ingress
  namespace: voltha1
spec:
  rules:
  - http:
      paths:
      - path: /
        pathType: Prefix
        backend:
         service:
           name: voltha1-voltha-api
           port:
             number: 55555

and then then voltctl can reach the cluster via "voltctl -s localhost:443 --tls <command>"
